Economic & Fuel Market Analysis During the Israel–Iran Conflict

Project Overview

This project is an end-to-end Data Analytics solution that analyzes the global economic and energy market impact of the Israel–Iran conflict using **Python, MySQL, SQL, and Power BI**. The dashboard provides interactive insights into fluctuations in oil prices, fuel costs, inflation, shipping costs, stock market performance, trading volumes, and crisis intensity across multiple countries.

The dataset was first preprocessed using Python, where data cleaning, transformation, and feature engineering were performed. The cleaned dataset was then stored in MySQL for SQL-based analysis before being connected to Power BI for interactive visualization and business intelligence reporting.

The dashboard enables users to explore economic trends through dynamic filters, KPI cards, line charts, bar charts, donut charts, matrices, and other visualizations, allowing decision-makers to understand how geopolitical conflicts influence global energy markets and economic indicators.

## Key Features

* Data preprocessing and feature engineering using Python (Pandas & NumPy)
* MySQL database integration for efficient data storage and querying
* SQL queries for business and analytical insights
* Interactive Power BI dashboard with slicers and dynamic filtering
* KPI cards highlighting key economic indicators
* Trend analysis of global oil prices (WTI, Brent, and OPEC)
* Country-wise comparison of inflation, fuel prices, and trading volume
* Stock market performance analysis over time
* Economic Stress Index and Crisis Intensity analysis
* Business-oriented data storytelling with interactive visualizations

## Technologies Used

* Python
* Pandas
* NumPy
* MySQL
* SQL
* Power BI
* DAX

## Dashboard Insights

* Monitored changes in global oil prices during the conflict period.
* Compared inflation and fuel prices across multiple countries.
* Evaluated crisis intensity and its relationship with economic stress.
* Analyzed shipping costs and global oil trading volume.
* Tracked stock market movements influenced by geopolitical events.

This project demonstrates the complete data analytics workflow—from data preprocessing and database management to business intelligence visualization—making it a practical portfolio project for Data Analyst and Business Intelligence roles.
